How the teams in the Alabama Sports Writers Association high school football rankings fared this week: 
CLASS 7A 
1. Bob Jones (8-0) beat Huntsville 45-14 
2. Spain Park (7-1) beat Oak Mountain 20-10 
3. James Clemens (7-1) beat Sparkman 28-0 
4. Hoover (6-2) lost to Vestavia Hills 20-13 
5. Central-Phenix City (7-2) beat Jeff Davis 43-14 
6. Theodore (6-2) lost to Foley 48-33 
7. Murphy (5-3) lost to No. 9 McGill-Toolen 35-28 
8. Buckhorn (6-2) beat Grissom 44-7 
9. McGill-Toolen (7-1) beat No. 7 Murphy 35-28 
10. Prattville (5-3) lost to Auburn 21-17 
CLASS 6A 
1. Clay-Chalkville (8-0) beat Woodlawn 72-6 
2. Spanish Fort (8-0) beat Daphne 35-13 
3. Opelika (9-0) beat Chilton Co. 50-6 
4. Muscle Shoals (8-0) did not play 
5. Saraland (7-1) beat LeFlore 41-6 
6. Benjamin Russell (8-1) beat Valley 53-0 
7. McAdory (7-1) beat Brookwood 48-12 
8. Park Crossing (8-1) beat Russell Co. 55-12 
9. Blount (7-1) beat Baldwin Co. 59-16 
10. Gardendale (7-1) beat Fort Payne 38-28
